<p>You might notice that the top and bottom of the â€˜Sâ€™ character are very parallel and exact. The cross bar of the â€˜tâ€™ character might appear right in the middle of the vertical line, whilst a native writer would be more likely to put it towards the top of the <dfn><a href="/penmanship-dialects/#-ascender" title="Learn more" id="--ascender" class="vocabwordinline m-textface bold yellowhover" data-definition-id="-ascender" data-vocab="">ascender</a></dfn>
